What am i going to get this time. Adds

What Is This Data?

This story explores the types and timings of YouTube ads logged by users during a specific period. We look at what kinds of ads appear most often, when they are most frequently shown, and how their lengths vary across categories.

The dataset comes from a class project involving manually logged ad details including timestamps, ad types, video context, and ad duration.

Ad Lengths by Category

We begin by examining the average length of ads across different ad types. Some types, like movie trailers and finance ads, tend to be longer, possibly because of their more complex messages.

Bar plot showing average ad length by category. Movie/TV and Finance ads are longest, while Gaming and Small Business are shorter.

What Types of Ads Are Most Common?

To simplify and clean the data, we grouped ad types using keyword detection. Heres how the ad types were distributed:

Pie chart showing proportion of ad types. The largest segment is Tech, followed by Gaming and Health.

How Long Are Ads in Each Group?

To explore variation, we visualised the distribution of ad lengths by category using boxplots and jittered points.

Boxplot showing spread of ad lengths by group.
